'''Lauro Escorel Filho''' (born January 5, 1950), most known as '''Lauro Escorel''', is an American-born Brazilian [[cinematographer]] and [[film director]]. He was born during his father, a [[Ministry of External Relations (Brazil)|Ministry of External Relations]], stay in [[Washington, DC]].<ref name=enci>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cqt35OogAQYC&pg=PA217 | title=Enciclopédia do cinema brasileiro |author1=Ramos, Fernão |author2=Miranda, Luiz Felipe | page=217 | year=2000 | publisher=Senac | isbn=9788573590937}}</ref> He first worked as an assistant to [[Dib Lutfi]] and [[Affonso Beato]], and made his debut in 1971 on [[Leon Hirszman]]'s ''[[São Bernardo (film)|São Bernardo]]'',<ref name=filmeb>{{cite web | url=http://www.filmeb.com.br/quemequem/html/QEQ_profissional.php?get_cd_profissional=PE291 | title=Lauro Escorel | work=Filme B | accessdate=April 30, 2014 | language=Portuguese}}</ref> which won [[Gramado Film Festival]] Best Cinematography Award.<ref name=gramado>{{cite web | url=http://www.festivaldegramado.net/premiados | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701061820/http://www.festivaldegramado.net/premiados | archivedate=July 1, 2013 | title=Festival de Gramado – Premiados | publisher=[[Gramado Film Festival]] | accessdate=July 25, 2014 | language=Portuguese}}</ref> He directed the short film ''Libertários'', winner of Margarida de Prata Award from the [[National Conference of Bishops of Brazil]], in 1976.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://37.mostra.org/br/pag/entrevista-lauro-escorel | title=Libertários deu rosto e sentido aos anarquistas de São Paulo | publisher=[[São Paulo International Film Festival]] | accessdate=April 30, 2014 | language=Portuguese}}</ref> In 1978, he would win again the Gramado Film Festival Best Cinematography Award for his work on [[Héctor Babenco]]'s ''[[Lúcio Flávio, o Passageiro da Agonia]]''.<ref name=gramado/> His first feature film, ''Sonho sem Fim'', won the Jury Special Award at the 1986 Gramado Film Festival.<ref name=gramado/> ''[[Ironweed (film)|Ironweed]]'' (1987), another Babenco's film, would make him more known internationally.<ref name=filmeb/>

==Selected filmography==
*''[[All Nudity Shall Be Punished]]'' (1973)
*''[[Lucio Flavio (film)|Lucio Flavio]]'' (1977)
*''[[Colonel Delmiro Gouveia]]'' (1978)
